Nov 18 2009 	Very good value but has a few tradeoffs	Our stay totaled three nights. The first one we payed for at roughly $35 for a king NS room. The next two nights were comp'd as part of a limited-time offer promotional package. So the room costs were quite low. The room was very large. The king bed was very firm and somewhat noisy. We did not have many problems with noise from rooms around us. TV channel selection is extremely poor; they definitely do not want you spending your time in the rooms. There is no wireless network coverage in the rooms themselves. There is free wireless in the coffee shop in the Casino area. There is cabled network available in the rooms, but it cost about $13 per 24 hour period. Several restaurants inside the hotel to choose from. We ate twice (breakfast and dinner) at the French Market buffet, which was very good. This hotel is about a half mile or so from the strip; I wouldn't plan on walking there. There is free outdoor parking available, but it can be quite a walk from the parking lot to the room elevators. Had spotty service from various staff. All were friendly, but sometimes slow to respond (bellboy) or otherwise just not helpful in resolving some issues (registration). Very nice fitness center with well-maintained equipment.	
