Nov 13 2009 	Great for the Price	This is the fourth time we've stayed there over the last 5 years and have found the hotel the best value for the price. The rooms are clean as is the hotel itsself. Check-in and check-out when smoothly and we encountered no problems with billing or our reservations. If your looking for luxury stay at one of the high price hotels on the strip as this hotel is not the Palms, Rio, Ventian, etc. and doesn't pretend to be. But for the price I don't think one can find a better hotel. Yes, it's off the strip but one also doesn't have to put up with the rush and crowds that wonder into the other casinos on the strip. Let's just say it gives you that small town feeling in a big city. The price is great as we got two nights comp and only paid $42.00 a night for the other two nights, granted it was Sunday thru Thursday but I couldn't find a hotel on the strip offering comparable pricing. Every year we say we're going to try another hotel on the strip but we keep coming back to the Orleans because of the price, service and cleanliness of the rooms. The rooms are not the fancy luxury rooms you find on the strip but who spends alot of time in the room except to sleep. I can guarantee you if the rooms were not clean we'd be staying somewhere else. The pool is nothing fancy but serves the purpose. We did find the casino area more smoky this time than our previous visits for whatever reason. We only ate at Fridays, the Courtyard cafe and the Market buffet at which the food and service was fine for the price, but I'm not a great fan on buffets. After many years I've come to the conclusion it's not one casino or the other that pays better but the slot machine you happen to be on as I've won on some of the slots and lost on others, it all comes down to luck. They have cut back on staff as I didn't see the cocktail girls come around as often as before while playing the slots. If you stay during the weekdays they also have limited live entertainment but we took the shuttle down to the strip and went to some of the other expensive hotels to watch the lounge shows. Like I said before if your looking for a luxury hotel and every amenity stay in one of the expensive strip hotels but if your looking for a clean, inexpensive, and friendly hotel the Orleans will fit the bill.	
