Oct 18 2009 	take this place if you go to Vegas	This place is definatelly the best value for money we've had. If you arrive Sunday through Thursday and book or prolong directly at the reception, they charge you only 35 USD + tax (whic is only 4,2). What a great deal!So for 40 USD incl. tax pr. night you get a big room, big bathroom, all clean, money box, TV (with around 20 channels) and many things to do. And many of the rooms have a view to the mountains - ours did as well.No breakfast is included in the price, but for 8,10 USD incl. tax you get a full buffet. Or else, you can take All-you-can-eat for a day for around 24 usd incl. tax, but our experience shows that if you got a full breakfast (they serve it until 10.30, where it changes to lunch buffet) you won't need lunch at all:)The place also had a couple of other restaurants, and only in 1 of them the staff was friendly and smily.They also offer fast food stations, if you're up for that, but it's not cheap compared to the buffet, where it's a lot of choice.The place is not near the strip, but they have a free shuttle that runs every 20 min to the center of the Strip. It takes max 10min, and I wouldn't pay 50 USD more just to stay closer to that. It really went easy with the shuttle.The casino is huge, both smoking and non-smoking areas available.They have movies and bowling, which we haven't tried.Very nice pool, actually 3 of them - regular OK big, childrens pool and a warm spa pool, really nice, not small at all.Free parking.Internet is only free at the coffee shop. Otherwise they charge you 12 USD pr. day.The only minus was that the waiters at the buffet (breakfast/lunch and dinner acailable) DO NOT smile. As if they don't have a good day every day:) We stayed there for 4 nights (although only planned 1 from the beginning), so we can compare.Definatelly great value for money.	
