Oct 7 2009 	A great off-strip value.	While celebrating my wife's 40th birthday, we decided to stay off-strip at the Orleans Hotel. The hotel was great, very clean, the room was very nice, and overall, it was a great value over staying at a higher-priced location on the Strip. We did get a renovated non-smoking room on the 13th floor, which had a nice view of the north Strip. Room was awesome, very comfortable, and better than our own bedroom at home. The room had a king bed, a couch, a chair, great bathroom, no complaints at all. The hotel offers a shuttle to the strip, actually there are 2 busses that make a loop to the Tropicana, the Gold Coast, and the Orleans, and they follow each other about 20 minutes apart. Got a breakfast buffet every morning for $5.49 (with a club card discount), how can you beat that? There is a $5/day resort fee, but that covers use of an in-room safe (loved it), in-room coffee (used it every day), 10 minutes of Internet access in the business center and use of the fitness center. I knew it going in, no big deal. The slots seemed very tight though, and we had no luck on the tables, but that's not the hotel's fault. Overall, don't really have anything negative to say, would definitely recommend this to a friend, and would definitely stay here again.	
