Sep 14 2009 	A Great Hotel at a Great Price	My friend and I stayed a couple nights at the Orleans after receiving an online offer that included a number of extras with our stay. We were skeptical but we decided to give it a chance after reading the reviews on Tripadvisor.Let me tell you - this is one hidden gem! This is a fantastic hotel with a clean atmosphere, tons of things to do, and at a price that can't be beat! The hotel features a newly renovated front casino exterior, but the actual hotel (usually not pictured) is older and dated. The rooms are a great size and include everything you need. The bed and room decor are quite modern and tastful. The television was a standard CRT tube but we didn't watch any. The hotels are almost the size of some suites, featuring a full bathroom, 2 beds, television stand, dresser, and night table. The rooms also have a nice sitting area with a loveseat and coffee table and chair, which is a nice touch and gives you an idea of room size. The hotel features a number of reasonably priced franchise restaurants, including Subway, Sbarro, Fuddruckers and Seattles Best Coffee Shops, amongst others. The Subway and Fuddruckers open 24 hours a day, which is nice for a late night snack. There is also a buffet for $7.99, which features a large selection of average buffet foods. There was nothing spectacular but also nothing that I disliked at the buffet. Other restaurants include TGI Fridays, the Prime Rib Loft, Big Al's Oyster bar, and Courtyard Cafe. A lot of selection for a relatively unknown hotel!I have a couple of complaints about the hotel: When we arrived we were met by a front desk clerk who was relatively cold and unfriendly. I find that this is an immediate turn-off, especially because they are the first face you see. Secondly, there is no free internet in the rooms. As I've written before, this bothers me because its a feature that so many other hotels offer at no cost. The hotel does offer free internet at Seattles Best, which was nice because I was able to enjoy a decent coffee and do my work online in a good setting. Overall, I was very happy with this hotel and would stay again. I wouldn't stay for more than $50/night because there are other options that are nicer for that price right on the strip, but on a sale or promotion I would not hesitate to stay here again.	
