May 15 2009 	The hidden value gem of Las Vegas	I love the Orleans in Vegas. Sure it's not the nicest hotel I've ever stayed in in Vegas, others like The Luxor or Mandalay Bay or even The Golden Nugget (maybe my favorite hotel in Vegas) are nicer with better places to eat but you can't beat the price at The Orleans, lets put it this way...three nights for 89.00 dollars total! Thats right you read it right. The also have a movie house, bowling alley and some pretty decent places to eat like Big Al's Oyseter Bar and Koji Sushi bar. Have also recently added a small food court. This hotel is really family friendly. I don't have any kids but if I did I'd stay at The Orleans all the time...movies, bowling, cheap eats without all the drunk tourists running around. The Orleans starr is almost always very helpful. The rooms are really decent size for prices that drop as low as $28 a night, I'd say about 450 sq ft. I've had some minor problems like a safe not working, or maybe the phone acting up but they are usually right on the ball with fixing any problems you bring to their attention. I highly recommend this hotel to friends all the time, I sing the praises of the orleans to anyone who asks about my frequent trips to Las Vegas. Has a pretty kick butt pool area too for a hotel so cheap. I'm telling you you can't beat it for the price.	
