Apr 20 2009 	A Great Place to Stay	This hotel is located off the Strip. It is a few blocks behind NYNY and offers very affordable rates. We only paid $34 a night, plus they gave us coupons for restaurants, bowling, slots. This was our second time staying here and we loved this hotel/casino. The Orleans is huge and the atmosphere is lively . The hotel has 21 floors and the rooms are clean and spacious. The beds are very comfortable. We had a great view of the Strip off in the distance. There is a free shuttle to the Strip, but we did not use it because we rented a car. There are many restaurants in the Orleans. The buffet is huge and reasonablely priced $8.99 for breakfast, $9.99 for lunch, and $13.99 for dinner. We priced the dinner buffets on the strip and some were as high as $29.99. The casino is huge, there is an arena for shows, a large bowling alley, a gym, a spa, a business center with 10 minutes of free internet per stay. and a movie theater. The pool area is pretty, but I don't think the pool is heated. If you are looking for an elegant hotel then the Orleans is not for you, but if you want an affordable lively, clean hotel/casino the Orleans is a great choice. One negative thing that I did notice was that the smoke in the Orlean's casino was more noticable than in other casinos such as the Palms, TI, and Mirage, but even still I would not hestiate to stay there again.	
