Mar 30 2009 	Well Worth It	I just spent 5 nights at the Orleans and found nothing lacking. Friendly staff all the way around. Now for a tip for those staying at the Orleans that have a car. Park in the ramp on the west side of the property. When entering the casino from the ramp take the outside path which will lead you to the elavators and easy access to the registration desk. If driving to the strip the best way is to follow the street on the westside of the property to Harmon. Turn left and go to Decatur and then turn right. Follow Decatur to Twain and turn right. Follow Twain all the way to you come to Industrial. Turn left and go under the freeway and come to the stoplight. Turn right on Frank Sinatra and then a left on Jay Sarno. This will bring you to Caesars Palace's parking ramp. Reverse the process to get back to the Orleans. Simple way to avoid traffic.	
