Mar 16 2009 	Nice hotel not such a convenient location...	This was my first trip to Las Vegas and the Orleans was a nice place to stay. First, what I did not enjoy was the fact it was off the strip, therefore not a good location for any first-time Las Vegas visitor. I would have enjoyed to stay someone on the Strip to walk around and sightsee or Downtown (as do many fellow Hawaii travelers). The taxi ride cost about $15 to the Strip area. =( What I liked about this hotel was their superior room service/customer service. The room service was very affordable, easily available, and speedy. Also when we requested a refrigerator (for a cost of $15 per day extra...) It was immediately brought to our room. It was also nice to have a window in the bathroom if you want some fresh air. The rooms and hallways are rather dated-looking and the lobby/casino area had a sweet perfume-like smell. Since this was my first trip to Vegas, I am not sure if this is the norm..... The buffet was okay, I wasn't quite impressed, but I can't complain since it was part of our hotel deal where meals are paid for. They have a TGI Fridays in the hotel which I enjoyed and they also had an asian restaurant there which was okay, nothing fabulous.	
