Feb 11 2009 	Nice Hotel Great Price But We Were Run Over By 600+ Children and Will Not Be Back	We just returned from a five night stay the The Orleans. Our first two nights were great. The rooms are large and the beds are comfortable. Lot's of restaurants and things to do on site making it really not necessary to go to other casinos. Initially our only complaint was the long length of the hallways in the hotel; most rooms are a long walk from the elevator. In addition, when you get off of the elevator there are no signs directing you to the appropriate room numbers. There are signs, but not right as you exit the elevator. We found ourselves getting off the elevator and going one way, then another until we found the sign that included our room number. Very confusing! The buffet food is just okay, nothing to write home about. On day two we received a memo in our room stating JAMZ was holding their national cheerleading competition at The Orleans Arena. In speaking with one of the parents, there were over 600 cheerleaders staying at the hotel for the competition. I am guessing the age of the cheerleaders were from five to thirteen. We have three children who are young adults so we are familiar with being around children. However, when we plan a vacation all year and go to Las Vegas, we do not expect Las Vegas to be like Disneyland! Children were yelling and running up and down the hallways. The walkways through the casino were packed with children, many of them without chaperones. When booking our vacation direclty with The Orleans, no one ever told us there would be 600 children staying there at the same time. When I mentioned this to the front desk clerk upon check out his response to me was, &quot;They have the same rights as you do.&quot; Yes, but at the time of booking no one ever told me there were going to be so many children at the hotel. Perhaps The Orleans knew if they told people there was going to be so many children staying at the hotel at the same time, we'd book our stay elsewhere??? When I told him we would not be back, his response to me as, &quot;I am sorry you feel that way, but that is fine.&quot; In these difficult economic time I guess The Orleans has plenty of business to go around and doesn't need our business. We are in Las Vegas generally 1-2 times per year and we will NOT return to The Orleans.	
Feb 2 2009 	Hard to beat for Value - Recommended!	Stayed here on January 23, 2009. We chose this hotel based based on the fact we were looking for a good, clean, and comfortable place to crash for about 5-6 hours after getting off the plane late on a Friday night and driving to LA very early the next morning. Close to McCarran Airport and no hectic driving up the Strip to another hotel - excellent in that regard.For the price we paid on a Friday night - about $40 all taxes and fees paid, the Orleans was a hell of a deal. The rooms are large and comfortable. Very clean and generally well kept. Furnishings are older and showing some wear, but our room on the third floor was still nice. Most importantly, bathroom was bright and very clean. Full couch and chair with coffee table in sitting area. Older, dated television set. Bed a little hard but both of us had a good sleep on it. Black-out curtains to keep the din of the city lights out. Great view of the strip if you're facing the east side. Lots of free parking but be prepared to walk.Check-in was very quick, once we found the front desk area (you have to wade through the casino to do so). This is a big place, so there was quite a walk to the hotel wing and then a long walk down the corridor where our room was located. The hotel section was quieter than I expected, though you should expect the odd straggler coming to or going from the casino floor, and thus hearing doors open/close.Services are in abundance...excellent choice of restaurants including propreitary establishments like Starbucks, TGIFs, etc. Place overall was well looked after and well staffed. I would definitely stay there again in the near future. As long as you don't need the excitement of the strip atmosphere, which is several blocks away, this is a good choice especially if you are value minded.	
