Jan 14 2009 	Great Room With a View of the Strip	I stayed at this hotel over the 2008-2009 New Year for 8 nights and was thrilled at how nice it was! It was everything that I had wanted out of a hotel. The room was big and clean, had a nice comfy king-size bed in a non-smoking room, and a gorgeous view of the entire strip (from Stratosphere to Mandalay Bay)! Service at both check-in/out and by the maintenance staff was friendly. The fitness facilities are really nice and are included in your stay. Too bad it was too cold to use the beautiful pool! The free shuttle to/from the middle of the strip was convenient and only took about 10-15 minutes. Best of all, my stay averaged about $50 CAD/night with taxes including my stay over New Year's Eve and Day, even after paying for the $5/night resort fee. (I had the Winter Sale special which included $20 Free Play and $20 Free Food Credit.) &quot;Funbook&quot; coupons for $10 match play and other miscellaneous things are given during check-in.Freebies in the room include a shower cap, toiletry kit (emery board, q-tips, cotton pads, sewing kit), shampoo, conditioner, and body lotion. The $5/night resort fee includes 10 minutes at the Business Centre daily, coffee/tea, unlimited local and toll-free calls, and fitness facilities/pool.For those of you concerned about past reviews that the safe is not bolted down, I think the Orleans has addressed this problem. The safe that was in my hotel room was bolted down so it was secure - I checked.New Coast Club Members get $5 Free Play when they sign up. Members get $1 off any of the affiliated buffets when they present their Coast Club Card. Members also get 7000 pts the month of their birthday, which is equivalent to $7 cash or $10 food credit. I just celebrated my birthday in December, so not only did I get the Winter Sale $20 Free Play and $20 Food Credit, I got another $5 in Free Play for being a new Coast Club Member and $10 food credit for my birthday! That was a total of $25 Free Play and $30 Food Credit! It's nice to be comped :) FYI - I won about $22 playing the slots using the Free Play!The lunch buffet at the French Market Buffet wasn't the greatest and I would probably only give it 2.5-3 stars out of 5, but the Champagne Brunch on New Year's Day was better and I give that 3.5 stars out of 5. The Main Street Station Hotel Buffet on Tuesday T-Bone Steak Night (4.5 stars out of 5) is so much better than the French Market Buffet, yet is also owned by Boyd Casinos, so I'm not sure why the food isn't better at the French Market Buffet. They should cross-train the chefs and that would make this hotel even more awesome than it already is!The cafe has an all day special of a double cheeseburger with fries for $3.99 that is pretty good (3.5-4 stars). The spaghetti with meatballs and garlic bread graveyard special for $3.99 is not bad either (3.5 stars).I would definitely stay here again and would recommend this hotel to my friends/family. It was not only a big room with a beautiful view, but a great hotel with an unbeatable price and good location close to the strip with free shuttles. Couldn't ask for a better hotel! I've stayed at the Paris twice before (once in a VIP suite with my family, and once in a regular room) and at Imperial Palace in a regular room in the past. I would say the Orleans was a much better experience overall (with the exception of the Paris VIP suite), since the amenities at the Orleans actually surpassed that of the Paris and the Imperial Palace. Paris and Imperial Palace cost more, did not include the gym or Business Centre, and their rooms and beds weren't as nice either. Sorry, I don't remember if they included coffee/tea or phone. Thanks to the Orleans for making this a perfect getaway!	
