Jan 3 2009 	Still The Best Value in Las Vegas - But Becoming Less Each Trip	Our family stayed at The Orleans for our fifth visit there between December 24 and 27 2008. The Orleans continues today to be the best value in Las Vegas - but the new owners have made some policy changes that are angering their guests and will soon drop the Orleans out of the &quot;Best Value&quot; level into a &quot;Sub Standard&quot; value. For example, they continue to have the largest rooms (925 SQ FT) with 2 queen beds in each for the least amount of money ($35 per night average) but beware what you sign and initial at registration. We were charged a mandatory extra $15 per stay per room for the safe which we did not use and for the shampoo that they say is special. I argued to no avail as they already had my signature and a copy of my charge card. The television service in the rooms has also changed. There are fewer regular channels available to make room for more pay pre view channels. The hotel &quot;has&quot; improved the exhaust system to rid the gaming area of cigarette smoke but the food at The French Market Buffet was absolutely horrible this trip. I hate saying that because I love buffets and The French Market was always one of my favorites. It is easy to see that the quality of food products has deteriorated. For example, the meats at the carving stations have a lot more fat content, the seafood is smaller portions with more bread coating to make it look larger, the deserts are less than grocery store quality, the restaurant was only 2/3 filled but service to clean tables was slow leaving guests in line longer than usual. These issues will likely send me back to a resort on the strip for our next trip. Why should I continue to pay extra for a rental car for the off strip Orleans Hotel if the food is so bad I have to go somewhere else to eat meals and the extra expense at check out is nothing short of extortion? Forget taking their shuttle to the strip because it is slow and the lines are very long. Taxi service is as expensive as a rental car so we always rent which allows us to come and go as we please.	
