Nov 10 2008 	Fine stay	My wife and I had previously stayed here and had a mixed result. However a cheap rate of $29 reeled us back in for another try.  Overall the results were much better. Check in was a breeze, we waited no more than three minutes to get to the counter. Once at the counter the clerk was efficient and gave us a wonderful room with a view of the strip (albeit a distant view). The room was fine and clean. The bathroom was clean and the A/C worked well. (I like it very cool at night). Granted this is not a five-star hotel and is showing some age, but the rooms suited us just fine. They are quite roomy and the bed was very comfortable but somewhat firm. I would like to state that in Las Vegas, how much do you really need to spend on a hotel room when you need only a few hours to crash and shower for the next day? (And we are well over 50) Only ate at Terrible Mike's for fast food and it was OK but typically greasy. Gambling went well since the Orleans has $5 craps table you can spend some time with little loss. The slots were also OK. Also on check in we got a coupon for $10 match play which I lost quickly and a 2 for 1 drink at any bar.  Check out with the video check out also went well, quickly and accurately since we had to rush to the airport and had to sadly leave the Orleans. In summary this is a great economical place to stay IF and especially if you have a rental car and want a clean comfortable place to stay in Las Vegas. In fact we have already planned to go back in Dec.	
