Nov 4 2008 	Very Nice 'Stay	My wife and I have enjoyed the Orleans at least once a year for the last seven years. We have always found it to be a good value given the location, accomodations, restaurants, and other amenities. In our years there , we have had no major problem. I am writing because we just returned from the Halloween weekend and would like to mention a couple of things.  First, one night we were woken up at 3 a.m. to the sound of what sounded like a loud buzzing, an almost electric vibrating sound. it seemed to be originating near the door. I inspected the area and found that it was actually air currents passing between the door and the jam. The weather stripping in that area was vibrating due to the high winds that were passing through the hall. We endured that situation through the night, not wanting to bother the maintenance people so late. Next morning I called the front desk to inquire about it, and they actually were not of much help. They told me that it happens to a lot of rooms when the outside winds start to kick it up currents are drawn through the elevator shafts up to the floors, causing the doors to vibrate?...Anyway, they told me to stuff some towels under the door to keep the winds from coming through. I don't know if it helped because the winds died down the next day.  Secondly, think this hotel strives to provide everything that the average visitor might need on location so that they don't have to go any place else.. ,Restaurants, spa, theatres, bowling alley, arcade, gym, pool, etc. I think their goal is to keep you on site so you don't go and gamble at another hotel. None of these facilities are top rated, just adequate. That's just the way it is given the cost of things , and the fact that they really can't specialize in any one thing...It's okay, most travelers aren't going to need the higher end stuff, Lots of hotels don't have half of the stuff that the Orleans has. If we want first class stuff, I guess we book the Bellagio , Wynn, or the Venetian..... ka-ching $$$$So I guess I'm saying that we'd go back unless we find a better value someplace else...I hope that helps.	
Nov 4 2008 	Comfortable stay	I stayed at the Orleans Hotel &amp; Casino for 2 nights. The location is off the strip, but it is only a couple of miles off the strip. The room was clean and furnished and the view was pretty nice (we stayed on the 11th floor). I was surprised that the bathroom was roomy and clean, however there was no lock on the sliding door. The only thing I was not too fond of was the $5 service charge per night even though we did not make any phone calls or use the coffee machine. The pool was big, but it was shallow and closed early. I would recommend staying here if you are on a budget and want to get away from traffic and chaotic check-ins.	
