Sep 17 2008 	Absolutely Excellent for the Reasonable Price	Eight blocks off the strip but plenty of glitz. Spacious and very clean room had all the features, from hair dryer to phone in bathroom - all at 1/7 the price of the fancier strip hotel where my conference was held. Adequate pools but not fancy nor extended hours. Friendly and helpful staff at security stations by hotel elevators. Only hotel ever stayed at with brass bathroom fixtures! (Probably a mistake as they do show a bit how much care brass fixtures really require, but not at all grungy.) Parked in front rather than in suggested ramp and found several free drink coupons on car. Sign up for free Coast Club card even if not a gambler for discounts at onsite restaurants etc - and it includes a few free spins of the slots. Buffet food okay if very carefully selected, but suggest their other (popularly priced) restaurants instead - or wonderful neighborhood tavern directly across street: McMullans, with real Irish food and music and sometimes even stepdancing. Cons: limited number of TV channels; $5 daily 'resort' fee added on to posted or negotiated rates (includes free local and 800 calls). A neighbor complained of an odor similar to hair salon strongest near elevators (13th floor) and very faint in some rooms, but did not bother us and do not know of its permanence.	
