Sep 3 2008	Still a great value!	Stayed at the Orleans from 25-29 August -- this was my 6th stay at this hotel in 3 years and all I can say is that it's STILL a great value! Paid only $31/night for a room in the new tower (9th floor) with two queen beds -- and for some reason I was not charged the $5 resort fee, but who's complaining??? Also, had to request a refrigerator for my niece's medicine and there was no charge for that either. Staff was pleasant enough but I was disappointed to learn that they've done away with the coupon books! Pillows are still pretty wimpy, but I requested two extra and they helped out &quot;somewhat&quot;. Pool was wonderful, as usual, and my husband and I still agree that the Orleans pool is one of the best in Vegas -- no frills but clean and always with a chair available! Slots were tight, but there seemed to be a good crowd in the casino anyhow. Oh, didn't take the shuttle, but it looks like they finally put up a rope to help que the line .... that should make some folks happy. Highly recommend the Irish Pub next door -- the Tuesday night Trivia (8pm) is a family favorite. Will be back to the Orleans again at Thanksgiving --- hard to stay away!	
