Aug 19 2008	Excellent off-strip hotel	This is my new favorite reasonably-priced hotel in Vegas. Of course it isn't as nice as Bellagio, but my room was very nice and less than $50 per night. The room was very large and even had a sofa, chair and coffee table. The mattress was very comfortable, but it had one of those moisture-resistant mattress pads. I had to remove it because it made me sweat. There's a coffee maker in the room, an in-room safe and an ironing board. The bathroom was large and nice as well, and there was even a phone next to the toilet. They do charge a $5 per day per room &quot;resort fee&quot; which is silly (why don't they just charge $5 more on the room rate?). The fee includes phone calls, 10 minutes daily of internet use in the business ceneter, and use of the fitness center. The fitness center looks brand new and has new Nautilus equipment, plus many types of cardio equipment. There's also showers, steam room, etc. Maybe I was just lucky, but my room was very quiet, and I barely heard any noise from other guests. There's a big parking garage in the back which is a bit far from the rooms, but valet parking is free if you don't mind somebody else driving your car. It's about a mile or so from the strip, but they have a free shuttle. If you've never been to Vegas before, you'll probably want to be on the strip for all the action, but veterans would be very happy here.	
