Jul 2 2008 	Outstanding Value for Money !	I suppose its about expectations. Some people want 5 star hotel treatment but are only willing to pay 2 star rates. I expect good value, for the money I pay to stop at a hotel. Orleans delivers this in bucketloads. To put things in to context, I am mid forties, Vegas regular, who is fortunate to work for an airline and has stayed in far too many hotels in my life. (some on my company's budget and a few at my own expense.)I prefer to stay at lower cost hotels on my vacations, for two reasons, 1) I am paying. and 2) I prefer comfortable surrounding which have a fun atmspehere over the decadent prententious atmospshere of a 5 star hotel.Orleans rooms are large for standard Vegas rooms, they have their quirks, a sliding door for the bathroom which I was not to keen on, as it was noisy and I woke my partner every time I used it. The small window above the bath is strange but it give us a good view of the strip when showering. The decor and furnishings of the hotel may be slightly dated ,but it gives it a lived in feeling, which is homely and welcoming. The hotel is a clean hotelThe hotel offers several eating options all giving good value for your bucks. The French Market Buffet, breakfast and lunch options are exceptionally good value.The outdoor pool area might not have the high octane vibe of some of the other Vegas pools, but that for me was a good point. The actual pool itself, and accompanying children's pool / jacuzzi are more than adequate and the general atmosphere of the pool area is relaxed and friendly. The fitness room and spa facilities are excellent, OK, you have to pay a $5 resort fee per day per room, but the fee is well worth it considering the facilities provided. I have stayed in 5 star hotels with worse health/ fitness facilities.The Orleans staff are probably it's best selling point, everyone who I interacted with were polite, courteous and friendly. The clientelle of the hotel have been denograded in an earlier review, ( east LA Crowd) whatever that means ? I found everyone staying at the hotel perfectly acceptable people, who's only aim was to enjoy themselves. I actullay met a few east LA people ( they had been announced as coming from east LA when singing on the Karaoke). I dont know a thing about east LA or what that term is supposed to infer, but they were absolutely fine people, and I enjoyed their companyAs you are probably aware the hotel is off strip, but the shuttle is frequent and reliable (every 20mins aprox). Last shuttle returning to the hotel 12:30amThe hotel like a lot of Vegas hotels gets a lot busier at weekends, you will decide if this is a positive or negative depending on your views.Overall Orleans is a very good choice for people seeking a lower cost hotel in Vegas who are looking for a more laid back relaxed enviroment with a sizeable room, and plenty of on-site amenities and recreational choices. Things you should know :Don't try to walk to the strip , not a pedestrian friendly walk.Taxi from airport $25 that includes tipTaxi from strip $15 includes tipShuttle to airport $6.50	
