Jun 13 2008 	Great Service friendly quick to get around.	I knew from previous reviews that this is not a high end resort. However, having stayed at the 2 other resorts before, both big and high end...I really enjoyed this resort.Its not the kind of room you walk into and say &quot;this is the nicest hotel I have ever stayed at&quot; but it's clean, comfortable, beds are new and supportive, not hard. The restroom is a little strange, with the closet by the sink and a really heavy slidding wood door. The little window in the shower was neat. My room mate was a smoker so I could open it up and send the smoke out and it was nice to let the sun and fresh air in while having a shower.The front desk staff, buffett staff, cashiers &amp; housekeeping are all super nice.I had a 2nd floor room facing the pool. It was quick and easy to get to the casino, shuttle &amp; food.the shuttle came often and most of the drivers were fun and funny.The slots were loose at night, very tight during the day (for me anyway). The casino was busy during tournaments &amp; weekends, but the rest of the time I could get the machines I wanted. I am a super low roller and have a budget of $100 per day. I ended up spending $300 on penny slots &amp; walked away with $400 over all, so up $100 there.The pool area was nice, lots of shady places under the palm trees, but too many kids in the pool for me. The service at the pool bar was unfriendly, so I tipped accordingly.The buffet. I personally like quality over quantity so this buffet was a little lacking for me. The roast was typically overcooked and grisly &amp; the choices were limited to tacos, overcooked pasta, pizza &amp; overcooked corn on the cob. However, the salad bar was fresh and good, lots of fruit available and the dessert bar was great. Stay away from the eggs benedict, not good.The convenience store was open 24 hours and has everything you may need including advil, gum, soda &amp; snacks. Since it only take 2 minutes to get there from your room it truly is convenient.The liquor store is fantastic, great prices and 10% or 20% off with your club card. No need to go off resort to get your liquor or beer.We got a free breakfast/lunch buffet coupon for signing up for the club card.TGI Fridays was over priced for mediocre food.When we checked out the &quot;Resort Fee&quot; that everyone complains about didnt exist &amp; we were not charged the $15 per day for our fridge, Saving us $100 on that alone.The Business Services room was great, I went daily for my free 10 minutes of internet, never had to wait and the staff there were great.I have been back for 2 weeks and I have already received promotionals for $99 for 3 nights plus entry into the slot tournaments, so my low roller status actually means something to them.Overall I was very impressed with this resort. It's not high end, but its comfortable, relaxed and fun. Not the place to party or for the younger drinkin crowd. However happy hour 99 cent drinks is always fun.	
