rleans plays dumb about all of this. I have since searched and found other complaints regarding this, so I know it's not the first time they've ever heard about it. I also contacted the Clark County Dept. of Environmental Health who inspected and said that it was a violation to shut the water down without notifying them. The supervisor at the Orleans told the DEH that it was done on an &quot;emergency&quot; basis and that's why no notification was given, However, we checked in at 10 am and found the note then, so they had time.I'm sorry to see what was such a fun place become so dilapidated and run down in a short 10 years...	
