checked in, but when we were going to check out late Sat afternoon, the line was long. Apparently, they have a bowling center and a child care center that guests can use. Our DD was too young, must be 2.5 and potty trained, but it may be helpful for others. I called a service from the Concierge from another property and was quoted $45 an hour, 4 hr min. For the price, I feel like we got an excellent deal and I wouldn't mind staying at the Orleans again.	
