Mar 3 2008 	Great hotel for the price!	This was our fifth time to Vegas. We have stayed at Bellagio, Mirage and Stratosphere in the past. We spend very little time in our room, but the room was what we want in a hotel room - clean, roomy, good safe, coffee maker, iron, etc. The rest of the time we go to whatever hotel we want to gamble or go see shows in. The price you pay to take a taxi to where you want to go from the Orleans added to the the large amount of money you save when booking this room still comes out much cheaper then staying on the strip. You can still spend your time on the strip in those hotels during the day and not pay the huge room fee for staying there.The Orleans does have a free shuttle, but we did not try it.We arrived late on a Thursday night and had to wait about 10 minutes to check-in. The room we had pre-booked (King nonsmoking) was not available, but they gave us the offer to switch to 2 queens n/s with a better view. That was fine.The room had a safe plenty big (laptop fit inside). They have a business office where you can use a computer (charge per minute and to print). We just wanted to print our boarding passes and after we used the business office, I noticed a machine you could use (for a fee) just for boarding passes and check-in just off the main casino on the way to the elevators.It was a busy weekend (Nascar) but we could always find room at a table game (even the $5 minimum black jack). The hotel had a live band each night. They did cover music (70s, 80s, 90s, current) and it was very good.The 24 hour courtyard cafe was excellent for breakfast and either no line or a short one when we went. Don Miguels had 99 cent margaritas and half price appetizers from 2-6. This was a great deal. The appetizers are very good and big enough for a meal. We spent a total of $12 and got 2 margaritas, nachos and queisedas.The sports book is nice enough. We had planned to go to another hotel if we wanted a nicer one, but it met our needs. You have to pay $2 for the Daily Racing Form, but if you turn it back in when you are done, you get your $2 back.Check out was easy and we never had to wait in line to catch a taxi. We didn't swim in the pool (still a little early in the season), but we went out to look at the area and sit in a chair and it seemed like a nice pool area.Our room was cleaned promptly each day. The toilet, shower and bathroom mirror and sink area is all one, so it kind of stinks if someone is going to the bathroom, you can't really be in there doing your hair/make-up or whatever. It also used a sliding door to the bathroom area which wasn't the greatest. The shower was nice and hot and lots of water which is always important!For the price we paid, we were very satisfied with the Orleans. Next time we go to Vegas, if we get a good price, we would definately stay here again.	
