no. Before doing that, I called Paris and Housekeeping told me that they could put a &quot;cell foam pad&quot; on any bed that felt too hard. I took them up on it, and it worked perfectly the second night.Unfortunately, I had to forfeit my second night at the Orleans since there was &quot;nothing anyone could do.&quot; If you're accustomed to &quot;pillow top&quot; mattresses and need a softer bed in a quiet room to sleep well, this Casino will likely leave you very disappointed. The hotels on the Strip are more expensive, but I will always stay at one with better service that can accommodate my needs next time. Lastly, I'm attaching a picture of the &quot;pillow top&quot; mattress that I was assured I would be sleeping on before booking my reservation. Honestly, there should be a law against this!	
