Jan 29 2008 	Orleans is clean basic accommodations	Just returned from three nights. Stayed at Orleans for the first 2 nights. First the good: Check in was quick and efficient. Staff was friendly. Room was spacious just like pics on their website. Lots of dining options on the property. If you don't have a car, you still can eat. (we had a car but a strip shuttle is available if needed.)Now the bad: Bed not comfortable to me. Hard and mattress not as comfy as many hotels we stay in. The pillows are BAD. Kind of like airplane pillows on steroids. We asked for three more to be delivered to the room and a courteous housekeeping staff member brought them promptly. But, I bet they paid a buck a pillow. Bring your own! The bathroom has a sliding door and while spacious enough, it should have a door between the potty room and the sink for privacy. Be sure to close the bathroom door at night or else you will wonder where all the light streaming from the bathroom in the morning is coming from. It is coming from the cute little window in your bathroom! Overall this is a good budget hotel and we booked because I have been to this hotel several times just to play. This time I could win nothing in several days of slot playing. They have tons of video slots but most people seemed to be winning nothing. I know they must pay, but didn't this trip at all. THey have a busy and good poker room too. Overall a good value, but I will stick to the strip again next time for my hotel portion of the trip unless they want to give me really really cheap rates again.	
