Dec 21 2007	You Can Beat the Odds at The Orleans!	I just returned from my second annual trip to The Orleans and for those who are &quot;fiscally-conscious&quot; enough to stay off The Strip and use your money for gambling, this is the place to stay.Let me start with the bad stuff. Only 18 of our 50 states are totally smoke-free and I live in one of them. I can't take the smoke at The Orleans but that's a personal issue and the only negative thing I have to say about The Orleans.The good stuff.1. Our room rate was under $40 a night. I understand this is a special rate offered between Thanksgiving and Christmas which is the slowest time of the year in Vegas. Call the hotel they will tell you about it 2. The Orleans offers one-stop vacationing under one roof.3. There is an 18 screen movie theater with the latest releases. We saw I Am Legend which was released December 14, 2007.4 There is a bowling alley-I don't bowl, can't vouch for this5. There is a Chinese restaurant with the best won-ton soup (get the big bowl size) and a happy hour where the appetizers are reduced by 50%.6. There is a day-care for your children and an arcade-can't vouch for these I didn't use them.7. The elevators are fast I never waited more than 45 seconds for an elevator. I was on floors 1-98. Decent view in rooms numbered 01-45, even numbers only, For instance room 638 and 606. You get the mountains and a view of the strip, although there is a parking lot right below.9. VERY LOOSE SLOTS!! This place is frequented by &quot;the locals&quot; and I now understand why. The Orleans was running local television advertisements promoting the &quot;loosening of their penny slot machines.&quot; It's true; the people I was with were winning in the hundreds of dollars on penny slots!!!10. There are several different restaurants in this entertainment complex;: there is a buffet, a prime rib loft, Al's Oyster Bar, which features these big bowls of seafood dishes; I recommend the Gumbo and the Seafood Cobb Salad, TGIFridays, Ice cream, hot dogs/hamburgers, tand the Courtyard Cafe with the best link sausages. 11. This hotel is not for the &quot;shee-shee- boo boo&quot;crowd, but The Orleans is not a flea bag either. Standard Room size 450 square feet!!! This is with a King-size or two queen-size beds.12. Housekeeping did a good job. I never ran out of soap or towels. 13. The gift shop is open 24hours a day. They have gifts and goodies to sell.14. Express check out is available and can be completed via the telelvision screen.15. There is a free daily shuttle that takes you to and from the strip should you just have to go there. It runs about every 20 minutes. Make sure you get the shuttle going to The Orleans, check with the driver before boarding.16. There is a $5 per day resort fee that covers all local and toll-free calls made from the room. The use of the internet and free printing in the business center. I was even given colored paper upon which to print! 24-hour access to the fitness center, and the use of the coffee maker in the room.17. This place is safe for single women, that would be me. 18. Pool and jacuzzi are outdoors and open year-round.Okay I&quot;ll stop now. I can't say enough about The Orleans. Going here is the perfect Christmas/Hanukah/Kwanzaa gift. I recommend The Orleans for families, seniors, college kids, the fiscally conscious, chick-trips and singles.	
