Dec 19 2007 	If you get the right package price this CAN'T be beat!	The Orleans...a couple of miles west of the Strip...sitting all by its lonesome.But look again! You get one heck of a deal in the price and they throw in so much. I stayed there a couple of years ago and wanted to stay on the Strip. Higher prices made me look at the Orleans again and I'm glad I did.Last summer, I stayed here mid-week for about $ 54 a night. The reception is big hotel Las Vegas style...efficient, polite and not exceptionally friendly. The lines are too long, so they have to keep moving you through the cordoned area to check you in or check you out. So you have to understand that.The rooms are GREAT! I got a higher floor this last time with higher ceilings. The room decor is unbelievable for the price...normally, you would get a Travelodge for this price. The door handles shaped like alligators are hilarious, but once inside, it's a seriously comfortable room. A few times, I decided to snooze on the bed to get my energy and wound up sleeping a little longer, it was THAT comfortable.One weird thing about the room shape: generally, bathrooms are at the entrance to a rectangular shaped hotel room. Here, bathrooms are on the outside wall, adjacent to a sitting area. That's fine...it just means your bed won't be near a window. Different, but not offensive.They charge a nominal &quot;resort fee&quot; and kick in the local calls AND use of the health club, which is pretty darn nice. Many other Strip hotels charge $ 10 to $ 15 to use the health club/spa, and that's without any services such as massages and therapies.Disadvantages are few. Obviously, it's off the Strip, so you will have to have a car or rely on cabs. I always rent a car so I walk through this mammoth property to the parking lot or parking structure and go where I want to go. The biggest disadvantage was the food that I got to sample: in my pack of coupons was a reasonably priced dinner buffet which I patronized one night. It was very poor. Oh yes, there was food in abundance, but the quality of the dishes was absolutely dismal. Bleh! The expensive buffets at the Strip hotels are much much better and worth the additional charge.Overall, this is typically an excellent value!	
