Dec 8 2007 	Very nice stay	Booked a group of 42 people to stay in the Orleans thru group reservations. Got 22 rooms and were some snags checking in. Check in process would have went quickly if the person whom recorded our reservation would have put the information in correctly. Out of the 22 rooms, 3 of them were still occupied upon entrance and the hotel staff quickly changed rooms for our guests and comped them a buffet. Rooms were nice, big and clean. Housekeeping was excellent. I personally was on the 5th floor and found the hallways and wait area outside the elevator to be very well kept. I did notice many of our group was on the 2nd floor (a smoking floor) and the halls to have soiled carpets.Used the spa on the second day and it was very lovely except for the people working on the drain in the womens shower area. The spa desk person failed to mention that a man was back there and me and my three guests put on a little unitentional show for them. You would have thought someone would have informed us that he was back there. When I complained the second maintance person told the front spa person that she should have cancelled all the treatments for the day. The desk person said it was to late and that we would have to change in a treatment room. Being that the spa has limited hours...shouldn't they have done this work during the night? The maintance man told us they knew the day before of the problems with the drains and that someone should have had them in there during the night. Oh well, massage was great and just went to my room to take a shower afterwards. The area was impressive and would most likely use it again upon return....if there are no maintance workers hiding in the shower. Kudos to the woman at the Spa desk...she was sooo very friendly and apologized for the trouble. Her friendly manner kept us from demanding any comps for our inconvience. Ate at TGIF and the buffet. Not bad...not great. Was really wanting to eat at Canal Street like we had on our last visit but the staff was rather rude when we arrived at 9:30 to try and eat. They said they were closing and acted put out if they had to seat us. Closing time is 10pm (early in my opinion for vegas standards) We chose to eat at TGIF.Drink service for games was actually pretty poor in some areas, but once one finally came around and served you and you tipped well...they came back quickly. Found the casino to be clean and a fun atmosphere. Not overly smokey like some casinos on the strip. The security at the hotel elevators was nice. Used the shuttle to the strip a few times and it was quick and efficient. Very friendly drivers!! Front desk staff was very nice and helpful..even with the above mentioned snags...they went out of their way to help. Business center had an employee that doesn't seem to like her job. Very curt and short with people. Not rude....just not inviting like we found with the rest of The Orleans employees. All in all...a good, inexpensive stay at the Orleans. We liked staying off the strip and it was easy to get to it if we wanted.	
