Dec 1 2007	Good Value but some irks	Stayed for 6 days the weekend after Thanksgiving. The room were large and clean and quite nice but several things irked me to keep this from being a 4 or 5 rating.I had a Deluxe Two Queens Non-Smoking room but was assigned the room at the very end of the wing, making it quite a hike to the elevator and the ice machine.The room door's auto closer must not be adjusted right because it took quite an amount of force to get the door open.The brass bathroom fixtures were showing their age with tarnish and mineral stains. The shelves over the closet area of the bathroom had chipped laminate.The safe is not bolted to any structure and so is free to be moved.During the next to last night of our stay, the air conditioner had some kind of failure and made a very loud noise when it turned on. I did not bother to call hotel staff on it cause the night time temperatures in Vegas made the air conditioner unnecessary.One of the electrical outlets was not properly mounted to the wall and so moved around when you plugged and unplugged something from it.Only the malfunctioning air conditioner was above an annoyance because it actually woke me from my sleep a few times.The Orleans is a good value for the quality of the rooms, but it does have a few maintenance issues to address.	
